<section>
  <div class="wrap split rev">
    <div class="media"><img src="https://d8j0ntlcm91z4.cloudfront.net/user_3FbWkBIBY3yHx2BErgPM2PJzng4/hf_20260714_221810_8910bc4d-fdbe-495c-bbbe-7a78411a83e9.png" alt="A person sitting quietly by a sunlit window" width="1200" height="675" loading="lazy"></div>
    <div class="prose">
      <p>Domestic violence — also called intimate partner violence — is any physical, sexual, emotional, or economic abuse between spouses or partners. It can happen in any relationship, regardless of income, education, age, or background. Children often witness this violence, and are affected even when they aren't hurt directly.</p>
      <div class="callout">
        <p><strong>The Caring Place is here to help you. We believe you. It is not your fault.</strong> You don't need to have "proof," and you don't need to be certain before you reach out — an advocate can help you sort through what you're experiencing, at your own pace.</p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<section class="services" style="padding-top:0">
  <div class="wrap">
    <p class="eyebrow">Recognizing Abuse</p>
    <h2>What abuse can look like</h2>
    <div class="svc-grid-2">
      <div class="svc"><span class="ic"><svg width="26" height="26" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke-width="2" aria-hidden="true"><circle cx="12" cy="12" r="9"/><path d="M12 7.5v6M12 16.5h.01"/></svg></span>
        <div><h3>Physical</h3><p>Hitting, restraining, or any use of force meant to control or intimidate you.</p></div></div>
      <div class="svc"><span class="ic"><svg width="26" height="26" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke-width="2" aria-hidden="true"><path d="M12 3l8 4v5c0 5-3.4 8-8 9-4.6-1-8-4-8-9V7z"/></svg></span>
        <div><h3>Sexual</h3><p>Any sexual contact or act without your full, freely given consent.</p></div></div>
      <div class="svc"><span class="ic"><svg width="26" height="26" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke-width="2" aria-hidden="true"><path d="M12 20s-7-4.4-9.3-8.4C1.2 8.9 2.8 5.5 6 5.5c2 0 3.2 1 4 2.2.9-1.2 2-2.2 4-2.2 3.2 0 4.8 3.4 3.3 6.1C19 15.6 12 20 12 20z"/><path d="M13 9.5l-2 2.5 2.4 1.8L11.5 17"/></svg></span>
        <div><h3>Emotional</h3><p>Threats, humiliation, isolation from friends and family, or constant criticism meant to wear down your sense of self.</p></div></div>
      <div class="svc"><span class="ic"><svg width="26" height="26" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke-width="2" aria-hidden="true"><path d="M4 8a2 2 0 0 1 2-2h11a2 2 0 0 1 2 2v1h1a1 1 0 0 1 1 1v6a1 1 0 0 1-1 1H6a2 2 0 0 1-2-2z"/><circle cx="16" cy="13" r="1.4"/></svg></span>
        <div><h3>Economic</h3><p>Controlling your money, preventing you from working, or running up debt in your name to limit your independence.</p></div></div>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<section style="padding-top:0">
  <div class="wrap">
    <div class="prose">
      <h2>Learn more</h2>
      <p>The Power and Control Wheel, developed by the Domestic Violence Intervention Programs of Duluth, Minnesota, is a widely used tool for understanding the patterns of behavior abusers use to establish and maintain control in a relationship.</p>

      <h2>If you're not sure</h2>
      <p>You don't have to have all the answers to call. Our 24-hour crisis line is free, confidential, and here to listen — whether you're ready to talk about leaving or just want to understand what you're going through.</p>
      <p class="phone-cta">219-464-2128<br><span style="font-size:16px;font-weight:600">Toll-free: <a href="tel:1-800-933-0466">1-800-933-0466</a></span></p>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

